answerBox.snippet: 1985 D Penny Value Brown and red and brown pennies are generally worth no more than a cent. And even red coins in mint condition start at around a dollar. At MS65, a red 1985 Denver penny is worth around $10, and that rises to $50 at MS68. The finest coins to have been certified by the PCGS are MS69.
